attributes.comment:
The proposed fees are an outrage! How is people expect to pay for fees that high?
The fees in effect now are high enough and people are barely making end-needs to
be able to pay this. The fees going up will only make their economical situation
worst! IF the process time will change and speed up up to 1 month, then the fee
increase is merited, but if the process time will only decrease for 2-3 months, then
the fee is just a way for the Department to get more money and do the same job
in the same time. Right now, as high as the fees are, people are still waiting
pending on fingerprint and name checks, and the DAO are checking whenever
they feel like it. So the fee increase is NOT going to help at all.
